Notes.Title: System Call Overview
Notes.Content: System calls are an interface between user applications and the operating system, allowing the application to request services from the kernel. They are fundamental for enabling interaction with the OS functionalities.

Notes.Title: Components of System Calls
Notes.Content: The system call process involves resources such as the Runtime Environment (RTE), system libraries, and the kernel itself. Direct calls and system call mechanisms are also critical parts of how system calls operate.
Notes.Wrong_Content: The system call process involves resources such as the RTE (Compiler Library), APIs, and the kernel itself. Direct calls and system call vectors are also critical parts of how system calls operate.
